The paper focuses on deep learning techniques applied to image processing, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and image compression. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel framework that involves learning to explain the predictions of CNNs, which falls under the category of interpretability in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves generating a sparse mask over an input image, which can be seen as a form of feature selection, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also discusses the potential applications of the proposed framework in decision-critical systems, such as surveillance cameras, drones, and self-driving cars, which falls under the category of multimedia processing (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
